{{Infobox figure skater |name= Bernard Fox |image= |caption= |country= |birth_date=October 6, 1916 |death_date={{death date and age|1998|10|3|1916|10|6}} |partner= [[Joan Tozzer]] |formercoach= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[SC of Boston]] |retired= |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry | [[United States]]}} {{MedalSport | Pairs' [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalGold|[[1939 North American Figure Skating Championships|1939 Toronto]]|[[1939 North American Figure Skating Championships|Pairs]]}} }} '''Matthew Bernard "Babe" Fox''' (October 6, 1916 &ndash; October 3, 1998) was an American [[figure skater]] who competed in [[single skating]] and [[pair skating]]. His pairs partner was [[Joan Tozzer]]. They won the [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] pairs title in 1938, 1939, and 1940. Fox was the 1936 U.S. Champion in both singles and pairs on the junior level.<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title= BERNARD FOX CAPTURES TWO SKATING TITLES AT ARENA |url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article.aspx?ref=201594 |work= |publisher= [[Harvard Crimson]] |date= 1936-02-24 |accessdate=2008-06-06 }}</ref> He was a student of [[Harvard University]], class of 1938.
